&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Manager, Business Development will partner with other Business Development professionals in sourcing leads, doing research, and qualifying incoming opportunities. The role will lead prioritized RFPs/pitches and will leverage a suite of sales tracking and reporting tools in the areas of Consumer, Healthcare, and Technology sectors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In partnership with &lt;strong&gt;We.&lt;/strong&gt;’s Business Development leadership, manage incoming new business opportunities including qualifying opportunities against the agency’s criteria.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In addition to managing inbound opportunities, work with BD team members and sector leads on organic growth strategies and proactive pursuits by applying business development strategy, agency positioning and pursuit lifecycle management across multiple sectors and markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide strategic sales counsel to internal clients and partner to lead or facilitate all aspects of progressing qualified opportunities through to completion, ensuring high quality deliverables and client satisfaction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage active prospects - through every stage of the sales cycle from initial qualification to RFI/RFP development to pitch presentation creation, follow up and supporting the team on the close - by setting priorities and expectations, problem solving, communicating ongoing status updates to the team and ensuring follow up is taking place along agreed upon timelines, while anticipating risks, addressing gaps and adapting approaches to meet pursuit goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with BD senior leaders to manage and coach pitch teams to finalize presentation content and ensure each member of the team is ‘room ready’ to deliver with poise, presence and confidence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively recommend processes and materials that would benefit the agency and that don’t already exist as part of the Business Development infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
