&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;About Us&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At &lt;strong&gt;We.&lt;/strong&gt;, we&#39;ve spent decades at the intersection of technology and humanity, bridging the gap between what businesses create and how people experience those creations. We&#39;ve learned that beneath even the most unruly situations — whether it&#39;s a global crisis, an emerging technology, or a sweeping organizational change—lies a simple human need. That need could be for trust, connection, safety, or a sense of purpose. But it’s always there. And it is only by uncovering these truths that we can make real, meaningful progress.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior HRIS Analyst – Workday is a key member of the Global HR Systems team, responsible for the configuration, optimization, and ongoing support of the organization’s Workday platform. This role partners closely with HR, Payroll, IT, and business stakeholders to ensure data accuracy, system efficiency, and scalable HR processes across the employee lifecycle. This position serves as a subject matter expert (SME) for Workday and plays a critical role in driving system enhancements, supporting global HR initiatives, and delivering insights through reporting and analytics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Workday Configuration &amp;amp; Administration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead configuration and maintenance across Workday modules (Core HCM, Benefits, Compensation, Talent, Performance Management)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage business process frameworks, security roles, and system integrations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and test Workday bi-annual releases, enhancements, and new functionality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot system issues and coordinate resolution with stakeholders and vendors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HRIS Operations &amp;amp; Data Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure accuracy, integrity, and compliance of HR data across systems through audits and controls&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee complex employee lifecycle transactions and system configurations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage integrations and data feeds between Workday and downstream systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reporting &amp;amp; Analytics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, build, and maintain Workday reports, dashboards, and calculated fields&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver recurring and ad hoc reporting to support HR, leadership, and business decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze HR data trends and provide actionable insights&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Process Improvement &amp;amp; Projects&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to improve HR processes and system usability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead or support HRIS projects, including implementations, upgrades, and integrations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate business requirements into scalable technical solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder Partnership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with functional team leads&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide functional expertise and consult on system capabilities and best practices&lt;/li&gt;
