&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;About Us&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At &lt;strong&gt;We.&lt;/strong&gt;, we&#39;ve spent decades at the intersection of technology and humanity, bridging the gap between what businesses create and how people experience those creations. We&#39;ve learned that beneath even the most unruly situations — whether it&#39;s a global crisis, an emerging technology, or a sweeping organizational change—lies a simple human need. That need could be for trust, connection, safety, or a sense of purpose. But it’s always there. And it is only by uncovering these truths that we can make real, meaningful progress.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We.&lt;/strong&gt;’s North America Health Sector was founded by experienced leaders seeking a fresh approach. Recognized as “Outstanding Agency Practice” at the 2025 U.S. PRWeek Healthcare Awards, and as one of the 30 best healthcare PR Agencies in the world by PRovoke media in 2026, our team continues to grow and deliver award-winning work.&amp;nbsp; We. offer comprehensive communications services to clients in pharma/biotech, life sciences, healthcare benefits/insurance, MedTech, healthcare IT and consumer health. We create programs that engage physicians, advocates, patients, regulators, policymakers, payors, and consumers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced Vice President to lead client accounts and play an important role in the growth of our Health Sector.&amp;nbsp; The VP will report to the EVP of Global Growth &amp;amp; Integration and will support select new business initiatives and sector operations.&amp;nbsp; The VP will also work closely with our EVP of the NA Heath Sector, SVP of Health Media and partner with leaders across the agency to drive integrated work and greater collaboration, including with our Consumer Sector, Tech Sector, Corporate Reputation &amp;amp; Brand Purpose (CRBP) Sector and &lt;strong&gt;We.&lt;/strong&gt; Studio, the creative hub of our agency.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is a seasoned agency professional with deep experience working in healthcare, navigating the complexities of a highly regulated industry across several different therapeutic and/or service areas, with clients of all stages and sizes. Must have experience working with pharmaceutical companies, with a demonstrated ability to counsel clients and guide teams through FDA regulatory milestones, data communications, promotional campaigns, and digital/social initiatives. The ideal candidate also has experience working across other parts of the healthcare ecosystem, plus a strong understanding of the policy issues affecting the industry at large.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Come join us at a different kind of healthcare practice and be part of a leadership team helping clients communicate their advancements in science, technology and more in bold, unconventional ways.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;The preference is for this candidate to be based on the East Coast, ideally in New York City or Boston.&amp;nbsp; Consideration will be given to candidates outside this region. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
